==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bluebird
<hw>Blue"bird`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small song bird (<spn>Sialia sialis</spn>), very common in the
United States, and, in the north, one of the earliest to arrive in
spring. The male is blue, with the breast reddish. It is related to the
European robin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pairy bluebird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
brilliant Indian or East Indian bird of the genus <gen>Irena</gen>, of
several species.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>blue-blind</ent>⟦br⟧
